This #disabled #bipolar man living in #poverty is ending 2023 -$300 and that means I can in no way afford life. Please Help me raise $1200, which will allow me to get current and get #food to eat, and pay rent.  I live in constant physical pain, as all over full body constantly hurting pain. Over the past few years as I get older it is getting much worse, and my bed desperately needs a new mattress, but this #disabled #bipolar man lives in #poverty and cant afford to replace it, but the past few months I have gotten very little sleep, one because my #anxiety has been getting worse, but also because laying down on my sunken mattress really makes my pain worse, and no I dont have a chair to sleep in. In the first spot on my #amazonwishlist is a mattress will you all help me obtain it? https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/1MUVXODQ665D0?ref_=wl_share  someone please help ease some of my pain today.  At what point do you just give up? How long do you suffer and struggle, as you cry out for help that never comes?  How do you deal with being so overwhelmed, you cant even think straight? Where do you start, when everything is in ruins?  From being in extreme debt, to constantly struggling to have enough if any food to eat, to constantly worrying about your living situation, because time changes what you had planed, not having the support you really need, and being left to feel that the victim card only makes you look weak, but in reality you really are weak, your strength, will and resolve are gone, hope burned out so long ago you don’t even remember ever having any.  Emotions don’t change just because suddenly relief may come, but the emotions from suffering and struggling until it does is nearly unbearable.  Talking won’t help, because your not in my shoes, you don’t see with my eyes, and you cant really understand how bad it all is. From the outside it may look sad, maybe a little off course, but its never that bad. From the inside its so dark black would be light. I get you don’t think money will change things for me. But raising the money I need, will enable me to eat, which will give me strength to face the day, money will allow me to pay off my bills, which will allow me to breath without a weight on my chest, money will allow me to obtain property, build a home, that can be mine forever, giving me peace and security, see money right now, will help me get to where I can finally focus on fixing the rest of me.  I have been begging and begging, Please Help Me, but no one is listening, and no is caring.  I am currently -$$$ in my bank account, I have not enough food to eat every day this month, I am over $6,000 in debt, today $10,000 will let me pay everything and to buy food for the next 30 days, $3-5million will let me buy property to build my forever home, and if I raise only $3million, and Say I spend $1.5 to buy property, build a forever home, fill it with all you need to live, Id still have around $1.5million in the bank, which works out to around $37,000 a year for the next 40 years, allowing me to cover taxes, utilities, maintenance, and normal life expenses, $37,000 a year is a great deal more than my current $12,000 a year, so yes money will and can help me, it can truly change my life.  I beg of you once more, PLEASE HELP ME Today, Please give Hope and Life via https://paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=GB6CYVMK53E4Y Thank You, a desperate and broken man.  I know that times are tough for everyone right now, but even a small #donation can make a big difference in my life. Your support will help me to pay for basic necessities like #food, #clothing, and #shelter. It will also help me to cover the cost of #transportation to and from important appointments, such as shopping for food and #groceries and what ever else may arise that requires me to get out and about. Living with bipolar disorder is challenging, but it doesn't have to define me. I am a determined and hardworking individual, and I am committed to living a fulfilling life. Help me to find and maintain #housing: Having a safe and stable place to live is essential for my well-being. Your donation would help me to maintain housing, so that I can focus on my #recovery and my goals for the future. I am grateful for any support that you can offer.
